.ll|Kōryō, Nara|ja|広
陵町}}, {{ill|Kashiba|ja|香芝市|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Yamatotakada|ja|大和高田市|12=draft|12=draft}} in Nara Prefecture. The cluster is situated along the Umami Hills and its * {{ill|Tsukiyama Kofun (disambiguation)|ja|築山古墳|12=draft|12=draft}} (Yamatotakada, Middle Kofun Period, keyhole-shaped, total length 210 m). ... 6 KB (745 words) - 21:16, 15 January
